comment:
* A mapping from String keys to values of various types. In most cases, you

 * {@link PersistableBundle} subclass.

variables.name: FLAG_DEFUSABLE
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating that this Bundle is okay to "defuse." That is, it's okay * for system processes to ignore any {@link BadParcelableException} * encountered when unparceling it, leaving an empty bundle in its place. *

* This should only be set when the Bundle reaches its final * destination, otherwise a system process may clobber contents that were * destined for an app that could have unparceled them.

variables.name: mParcelledData
variables.comment:
* If mParcelledData is non-null, then mMap will be null and the
     * data are stored as a Parcel containing a Bundle.  When the data
     * are unparcelled, mParcelledData willbe set to null.

variables.name: mParcelledByNative
variables.comment: * Whether {@link #mParcelledData} was generated by native coed or not.

variables.name: mClassLoader
variables.comment: * The ClassLoader used when unparcelling data from mParcelledData.
